  "prompt": "Is machine made egg veg or non veg?",
  "response": "Machine-made eggs, also known as synthetic or artificial eggs, can vary in their ingredients and production process. Generally, synthetic eggs are formulated to resemble real eggs and may use plant-based or chemical components. If they are made entirely from plants or chemicals without any animal-derived ingredients, they would be classified as vegetarian. However, if any animal products are used in the production of these artificial eggs, they would be considered non-vegetarian. Always check the ingredient list to determine the classification.",
